The argument over Apple and Google's plan to use Bluetooth to help with Covid-19 contact tracing escalated this week.
San Francisco International Airport employee websites were hacked in March.
Airport officials forced a password reset, and encouraged any third-party visitors to those sites to do so as well.
As part of Microsoft's regular Patch Tuesday release, the company fixed three Windows zero-day exploits that were being actively exploited by hackers.
Of the 100 million phishing emails that route through Google's email system every day, 18 million are coronavirus or Covid-19 related.